==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*murþran'' (Gothic [[𐌼𐌰𐌿𐍂𐌸𐍂]]), from Indo-European ''*mr̥-tro-'', from ''*mr̥-'' ‘die’ (Latin [[mors]], Old Irish [[marb]]).  Compare [[morþ]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'moɹðoɹ/

===Noun===
'''morþor''' ''n'' or ''m''
# [[murder]]
# a great [[sin]] or [[crime]]

===Related words===
*[[morþ]]

